    <snippet id="json-fallback-doesnt-allow">
        Out of the box, Laravel
        <a
            href="https://github.com/laravel/framework/issues/41565#issuecomment-1073572954"
            target="_blank">doesn't allow</a>
        fallback translations for JSON keys.
        For example, when you call <code>__('Remember Me')</code>, you get <code>Remember Me</code> instead of
        <code>Se souvenir de moi</code> for French fallback language.
    </snippet>

    <snippet id="json-fallback-doesnt-need">
        <warning>
            If you use English as a fallback localization, then you do not need to use this package.
        </warning>
    </snippet>

